modules.description: The module provides operations for constructing, modifying, and querying maps with key-value pairs, including adding, removing, updating, and merging entries, as well as iterating or filtering bindings. It works with maps featuring typed keys (e.g., strings) and generic values, supporting ordered traversal and sequence-based construction. Use cases include processing structured data, aggregating results from sequences, or managing configuration settings with string-based keys.

Provides functions to decode JSON values with conditional logic, including checking field types, contents, or decoding failures. Works with JSON values, records, and custom data types defined by the user. Enables precise control over parsing, such as transforming nested JSON into a specific domain model or handling optional fields based on presence.

Handles key-value mapping with string-typed keys and arbitrary values, enabling dynamic data manipulation through addition, removal, and merging of entries. Supports ordered iteration, filtering, and sequence-based construction for structured data processing. Operations include updating bindings, traversing maps, and combining multiple mappings. Example tasks include parsing configuration files, aggregating query results, or maintaining stateful data structures.
